# Components Guide

## WordPress Theme Structure
- `header.php` - Main header with navigation
- `footer.php` - Site footer
- `functions.php` - Theme setup and functionality
- `index.php` - Main template file
- `front-page.php` - Homepage template
- `page.php` - Default page template
- `single.php` - Single post template
- `archive.php` - Archive template
- `404.php` - Error page template

## WooCommerce Templates
- `woocommerce/archive-product.php` - Shop page
- `woocommerce/single-product.php` - Single product
- `woocommerce/content-product.php` - Product loop item
- `woocommerce/cart/cart.php` - Cart page
- `woocommerce/checkout/form-checkout.php` - Checkout page

## Navigation
The main navigation is consistent across all pages and includes:
- Logo
- Responsive menu toggle for mobile
- Main navigation links with dropdowns
- Search bar
- User account and cart icons
- WordPress menu registration:
```php
register_nav_menus([
  'primary' => __('Primary Menu', 'zensecrets'),
  'footer' => __('Footer Menu', 'zensecrets')
]);
```

## Product Cards
Product cards follow a consistent structure:
```php
<article <?php wc_product_class('product-card'); ?>>
  <div class="product-card__image-container">
    <?php woocommerce_template_loop_product_thumbnail(); ?>
  </div>
  <div class="product-card__content">
    <h3 class="product-card__title"><?php the_title(); ?></h3>
    <div class="product-card__footer">
      <div class="product-card__price"><?php woocommerce_template_loop_price(); ?></div>
      <?php woocommerce_template_loop_add_to_cart(); ?>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
```

## Product Slider
The product slider component includes:
- Multiple slides with product grids
- Navigation arrows (prev/next)
- Dot indicators
- ARIA roles for accessibility
- WooCommerce product query integration

## Footer
The footer is divided into sections:
- Instagram social section
- Institutional links
- Contact information
- Payment methods
- Shipping information
- Copyright and credits
- WordPress widget areas:
```php
register_sidebar([
  'name' => __('Footer Widget Area', 'zensecrets'),
  'id' => 'footer-widget-area',
  'description' => __('Add widgets here to appear in footer', 'zensecrets')
]);
```

## Category Tags
Category tags are used for quick navigation:
```php
<section class="category-tags">
  <div class="tags-container">
    <?php
    $product_categories = get_terms('product_cat');
    foreach ($product_categories as $category) {
      printf(
        '<a href="%s" class="category-tag">%s</a>',
        esc_url(get_term_link($category)),
        esc_html($category->name)
      );
    }
    ?>
  </div>
</section>
```
